To generate the puzzle in HTML format, we can use JavaScript to parse the XML code and create a table element with the appropriate number of rows and columns, and then add the words to the table as individual cells. Here's an example JavaScript code that does this:
```
// Parse the XML code
var xml = "<puzzle><title>Crossword Puzzle</title><description>Test your knowledge with this fun crossword puzzle!</description><size rows='5' columns='5'/><words><word x='1' y='1' direction='across'>cat</word><word x='3' y='1' direction='across'>dog</word><word x='2' y='2' direction='down'>rat</word><word x='4' y='2' direction='down'>bat</word><word x='1' y='3' direction='across'>pig</word><word x='3' y='3' direction='across'>cow</word><word x='5' y='3' direction='across'>hen</word><word x='2' y='4' direction='down'>fox</word><word x='4' y='4' direction='down'>owl</word></words></puzzle>";
