The `CalculateComplementaryColor`, `CalculateAnalogousColors`, and `CalculateTriadicColors` methods use the HSB (hue, saturation, brightness) color model to calculate complementary, analogous, and triadic colors, respectively.
The `ColorFromHsb` method converts HSB values to RGB values. It uses the `HueToRgb` method to calculate the red, green, and blue components of the color.
