Improving color and texture recognition of puzzle pieces using Java can be achieved using several algorithms and techniques. One of the most popular and effective techniques is the watershed algorithm. 
The watershed algorithm is a technique used for image segmentation. It works by treating the image as a topographic map, where the brightness of each pixel represents the height of the terrain. The algorithm then floods the map from the lowest points until the entire image is segmented into regions.
To implement the watershed algorithm in Java, you can use the OpenCV library. Here is some sample code:
```
import org.opencv.core.Core;
import org.opencv.core.Mat;
import org.opencv.core.CvType;
import org.opencv.core.Scalar;
import org.opencv.imgproc.Imgproc;
public class WatershedSegmentation {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        // Load the image
        Mat image = Imgcodecs.imread("puzzle.jpg");
        // Convert the image to grayscale
        Mat gray = new Mat();
        Imgproc.cvtColor(image, gray, Imgproc.COLOR_BGR2GRAY);
        // Apply thresholding to obtain a binary image
        Mat binary = new Mat();
        Imgproc.threshold(gray, binary, 0, 255, Imgproc.THRESH_BINARY_INV + Imgproc.THRESH_OTSU);
        // Apply the distance transform to obtain a distance map
        Mat distance = new Mat();
        Imgproc.distanceTransform(binary, distance, Imgproc.DIST_L2, 3);
        // Apply the watershed algorithm to segment the image
        Mat markers = new Mat();
        Imgproc.connectedComponents(binary, markers);
        Core.convertScaleAbs(markers, markers, 10, 0);
        Imgproc.watershed(image, markers);
        // Display the segmented image
        Mat result = new Mat();
        Core.addWeighted(markers, 0.5, image, 0.5, 0, result);
        Highgui.imwrite("result.jpg", result);
    }
}
```
This code loads an image called "puzzle.jpg", converts it to grayscale, applies thresholding to obtain a binary image, and then applies the watershed algorithm to segment the image. The resulting segmented image is saved as "result.jpg".
