Here's an implementation of the bubble sort algorithm in C++:
```
void bubbleSort(int arr[], int n) {
    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1; i++) {
        for (int j = 0; j < n - i - 1; j++) {
            if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                int temp = arr[j];
                arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                arr[j + 1] = temp;
            }
        }
    }
}
```
To optimize this implementation, you can add the following techniques:
1. Add a flag to check if any swaps were made during a pass through the array. If no swaps were made, then the array is already sorted and the algorithm can exit early. This can be done by adding a boolean variable `swapped` and setting it to `false` before the inner loop. If a swap is made, set `swapped` to `true`. After the inner loop, check if `swapped` is still `false` and exit the outer loop if it is.
2. Use a while loop instead of a for loop for the inner loop. This can be done by initializing `j` outside the loop and incrementing it inside the loop. This can be more efficient because it avoids the overhead of checking the loop condition on each iteration.
3. Use a flag to track the last swapped index. Since the last swapped index indicates that all elements after it are sorted, we can avoid comparing them again in subsequent passes through the array. This can be done by adding an integer variable `lastSwappedIndex` and setting it to `n - 1` before the outer loop. After the inner loop, set `lastSwappedIndex` to the index of the last swap. In subsequent passes, the inner loop can stop at `lastSwappedIndex` instead of `n - i - 1`.
Here's an optimized implementation of the bubble sort algorithm in C++:
```
void bubbleSort(int arr[], int n) {
    bool swapped = true;
    int lastSwappedIndex = n - 1;
    for (int i = 0; i < n - 1 && swapped; i++) {
        swapped = false;
        int j = 0;
        while (j < lastSwappedIndex) {
            if (arr[j] > arr[j + 1]) {
                int temp = arr[j];
                arr[j] = arr[j + 1];
                arr[j + 1] = temp;
                swapped = true;
                lastSwappedIndex = j;
            }
            j++;
        }
    }
}
```
